ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, the FL spectra of DE-P-CDs were examined in the presence of varying concentrations of TC. The FL intensity was obtained with an excitation wavelength of 400 nm. The FL intensity of the dual emissive sensor was dramatically decreased by adding TC, and a standard calibration graph was fabricated as shown in Fig. 6
                        . The linear dynamic range spanned from 25 to 275 μM with a limit of detection (LOD) of 5.78 μM and a limit of quantification (LOQ) of 19.28 μM, at the emission peak of 486 nm, while at 616 nm the linear dynamic range was from 25 to 275 μM with a LOD of 6.18 μM and LOQ of 20.95 μM. In comparison to previous fluorescent methods for TC determination, the probe exhibits superior detection performance (refer to Table 1
                        ).
